I'm no expert but I would guess without even checking the error log, simply by looking at your list of mods installed that you are hitting the memory barrier. When you next start up KSP open up task manager and watch your RAM usage for the game. Mine will crash no matter what at anything above 3.2Gb.

Also next time put the log in spoiler tags. Saves the scrolling.

Tweety

Edit: if you keep hitting memory issues try forcing the game to open [-forceopengl](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/84203-Less-memory-usage-by-using-OpenGL) or maybe [Active Texture Management](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/59005-0-90-Release-4-3-Dec-16-2014-Active-Texture-Management-Save-RAM!).

List of stuff installed in my main game at the moment. Only crashes with memory issues when either I'm using the VAB/SPH a lot, or near Kerbin. Which is basically saying "when I trigger memory leaks". Look no ATM!

noobs: I'd recommend trying opengl and dx11 and probably switching between depending what you're doing - you can't use Minmus or Ike under dx11 at the moment, but opengl doesn't have shadows and can give some odd slowdowns so best not used on other planets. Landing without shadows can get a bit wierd. Squad mentioned DX11 improvements in 1.0, so hopefully it'll be fully usable soon. Saves me 1GB or so of memory once textures are loaded & dumped to VRAM.
